window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>You will find delight in this unconventional romance story, penned by a debut novelist, which vividly captures the lush tropical atmosphere and the complexities of luxury community romances and interrelationships in contemporary Boca Raton, Florida. The story revolves around the Royal Azalea Villas Welcoming Committee, comprised of three main characters: the spirited single woman Raine, the charming divorcee Michelle, and the attractive widow Alice. Their lives take an intriguing turn when they all seek the attention of Brad, a tall, very fit, and undeniably handsome new resident in the same court. What drama will unfold from this situation? Find out when you delve into their lives, discover humor alongside tension, and enjoy unexpected twists that will keep you listening late into the night.</p>"; 
